The candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has taken an early lead in the ongoing collation of votes at the Bayelsa governorship election. The APC leads it’s closest rival, the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), winning four out of the five local government election results announced so far. The results of the five local so far announced are below: Yenagoa
A – 363
PDP – 19,184
APC – 24,607 Brass LGA
APC – 23,831
PDP – 10,410 Kolokuma/Opokuma
PDP – 15,360
APC 8,934 Nembe LGA
A – 261
APC – 83, 041
PDP 874 Sagbama LGA
A – 131
APC – 7, 831
